# Terms
Quadratic T complexity   O(n²)
Linear T complexity      O(n)
Logarithmic T complexity O(log n)
Constant T complexity    O(1)

What Can Cause Time in a Function ?
- I/O operations: Reading/writing data takes time
- Deep Recursion can significantly increase execution time
- Loops: (for, while)
- Function calls: Each call adds overhead
- Comparisons: (>,<,!=)
- Number of Operations:  (+,-,*,/)
- Data Structure Operations..
- Algorithmic Complexity..

Space complexity measures an algorithm's temporary RAM usage
What Causes Space Complexity ?
- DS
- Auxiliary Space: Extra memory used for temporary data structures, buffers, or additional variables during computation
- Function Calls
- Dynamic Allocations: malloc ?
- Variables

